## Data Accumulation and Compounding

The real power of autoresearch isn’t any single experiment — it’s the **data that accumulates**. Each run produces data. That data enables deeper analysis. Deeper analysis enables better experiments. This is the recursive part.

```
Week 1:    Basic data → Basic analysis → Baseline metric
Week 4:    4 weeks of data → Trend analysis → Better signals
Week 12:   3 months of data → Correlation analysis → Pattern detection
Week 26:   6 months of data → Predictive models → Confidence scoring
Week 52:   1 year of data → Backtesting → Validated methodology
```

**Design your data store for compounding.** Every observation should be queryable later. Don’t throw away intermediate data. Store it structured (database), not just as prose (markdown reports).

