## Origin

This methodology is extracted from [karpathy/autoresearch](https://github.com/karpathy/autoresearch) (March 2026), where Andrej Karpathy applied it to autonomous neural network training research. The core insight — give an AI agent a fixed evaluation harness and let it experiment autonomously — generalizes far beyond ML training.

Karpathy’s words: *“The idea: give an AI agent a small but real setup and let it experiment autonomously overnight. It modifies the code, trains for 5 minutes, checks if the result improved, keeps or discards, and repeats. You wake up in the morning to a log of experiments and (hopefully) a better model.”*

Replace “code” with “methodology,” “trains” with “analyzes,” and “model” with “research output” — and you have a universal self-improving research system.

